Class Colors.Morph

java.lang.Object
color.Colors.Morph
All Implemented Interfaces:
Category.Morphism<Colors.Obj,​Colors.Obj>
Enclosing class:
Colors
public class Colors.Morph extends Object implements Category.Morphism<Colors.Obj,​Colors.Obj>
Implementation of interface Category's generic interface Category.Morphism.  An arrow between two objects, the source and the target.  Morphisms are "processes", the possible ways to get from one value to another.  They can be composed: one can follow a process from an initial value to an intermediate value, and then follow a second process to a final value, and consider the two processes together as a single composite process.

  • Constructor Details

    • Morph

      Morph​(Colors.Obj source, Colors.Obj target) throws InvalidColorException
      Class constructor. Takes as parameters two objects of type Colors.Obj and initializes the class fields corresponding to:
      • the objects themselves
      • their identification numbers
      • the average color between those of the two objects, that is going to be used to color the arrow between the two nodes in the graph representation.
      Parameters:
      source - the object where the morphism starts
      target - the object where the morphism ends
      Throws:
      InvalidColorException - If the RGB values provided to the Color's constructor do not fall within the allowed range (0-1).
